[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926750&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781926750&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

While looking into installing a BIND name server here, I have
noticed some peculiarities that might be worth mentioning here.

The sample databases in the BIND operations guide list HINFO
records with a class of "ANY".  Is this legal ?  Are wildcard
classes allowed in resource records, or only in queries ?

The other issue is how queries with incomplete domain names are
interpreted by the server if they are not found.  If the name
you use in a query does not contain a ".", the BIND server will
append it's domain to the query.  So if you send a query to the
Berkeley.EDU server of "monet", it will return information for
monet.Berkeley.EDU.  Again, is this legal ?  Are name servers
allowed to resolve such queries in this manner or should they
fail ?


				Glenn Marcy
				System Manager
				Computer Science Department

